This man's brother-in-law was sent to investigate the Anahuac Disturbances. That relative, Martín Perfecto de Cos, surrendered at the Siege of Béxar. This man led an uprising during the Casa Mata Plan Revolution, leading to the fall of the emperor Agustín de Iturbide. As he rose to power, this man defeated the Barradas Expedition and formalized the "Siete Leyes".
